Here are the shell commands that I used to go through the exercise:

$ git checkout -b work
[ Edit indict to add feature, test, "discover" FPR bug ;
  edit bloom.py to fix bug, test, confirm bugfix ;
  edit README to document the new feature and change the version to 2.0. ]
$ git add bloom.py
$ git ci -m "bloom: in retrospect, I distrust the spirit vision"
$ git add indict
$ git add -p README
[ Only stage the documentation part of the changes ]
$ git ci -m "indict: add a '-f' option to print out the false-positive rate" \
         -m "Also document it in README."
$ git ci -a -m "Bump the version to 2.0"
$ git checkout master
$ git merge work
$ git tag v2.0

The commits that I made are in the history of this branch.
